en_223461_0	The head of the terrorist who attacked the Zion Church on Easter Sunday, buried in the Kalliyankadu Hindu cemetery in Batticaloa has been exhumed.
en_223461_1	This was in the presence of the Batticaloa Magistrate A.C. Rizwan.
en_223461_2	The order was given by the Magistrate's Court recently based on the submissions of the Criminal Investigation Department.
en_223461_3	The Batticaloa Magistrate has ordered the District Secretary of Batticaloa to exhume the remains of the terrorist from the place where he was buried and to identify a specific location suitable for reburial and to deposit the remains in the new location.
